data.name: loadStateOpenToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: Open a rom, then load state for that game on selected slot (if there is state for that game in selected slot).

data.name: loadStateOpenRecentToolStripMenuItem1.ToolTipText
data.value: If set, the emu will load state for the game that opens from recent menu from selected slot (if there is state in selected slot for that game).

data.name: useEmulationThreadToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: If set, emulation will be running in separed thread. If not set, emulation run in video thread. It is recommended not to set this value unless there is problem with video renderer. REQUIRES GAME RE-LOAD, NOT HARD RESET.

data.name: regionToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: Emulation region settings. WILL HARD RESET IF EMU IS ON

data.name: resolutionToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: Render resolution. This is different from screen size which can be set using options above.

data.name: keepAspectRatioToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: Indicates if the emu should keep aspect ratio of the rendered image size

data.name: autoStretchToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: Indicates if the emu should stretch the window to the multiply that can be set below when a game is loaded.

data.name: stretchMultiplyToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: set the stretch multiply to use when the emu stretchs window

data.name: showFPSToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: Indicates if the emu should show fps

data.name: showNotifiacationsToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: Indicates if the emu should show notifications such as state saved, state loaded ....etc

data.name: vSyncToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: Toggle vertical synchronising. It is recommended to be enabled unless there are problems with video rendering.

data.name: startGameInFullscreenToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: If set, the video renderer will switch into fullscreen mode when you start a game. This is different from fullscreen option, which indecate the current window status.

data.name: sDL2SettingsToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: Change settings of SDL2 renderers only.

data.name: useMixerToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: If set, My Nes will use a mixer which is different from the one that described in the wiki (this mixer based on summing outputs then taking the averages). If not set, My Nes will use the mixer that described in the wiki.

data.name: toolStripMenuItem1.ToolTipText
data.value: Change settings of SDL2 renderers only.

data.name: enableGameGenieToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: Enable GameGenie for current game. This must be enabled in order GameGenie to work for currecnt game.

data.name: pauseEmulationWhenFocusLostToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: Indicates if the emu should be paused when the focus of this window is lost.

data.name: replaceSnpashotToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: Indicates if the emu should replace and limit the snapshot file for each game to one snapshot file instead of creating snapshot file for the same game each time a snap taken.

data.name: saveSRAMFileOnEmuShutdownToolStripMenuItem.Text
data.value: Save S-RAM file on emu shutdown

data.name: saveSRAMFileOnEmuShutdownToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: If enabled, emu will save S-RAM file for each game after emulation shutdown. S-RAM files will be saved at SRAM folder.

data.name: shutdownEmuExitMyNesOnEscapePressToolStripMenuItem.Text
data.value: Shutdown Emu/Exit My Nes on &Escape press

data.name: shutdownEmuExitMyNesOnEscapePressToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value:
When you press Escape button on your keyboard: My Nes will exit fullscreen mode if it run in fullscreen.
If you press Escape again, and this OPTION IS SET: If the emu is on, it will shutdown. If the emu is already shutdown, it will exit My Nes.

data.name: foldersToolStripMenuItem.ToolTipText
data.value: Change/Show folders that used for snapshots, state, sound records, game genie codes and s-rams files.

data.name: loadStateOpenToolStripMenuItem1.ToolTipText
data.value: Open a rom, then load state for that game on selected slot (if there is state for that game in selected slot).

data.value: If set, the emu will load state for the game that opens from recent menu from selected slot (if there is state in selected slot for that game).
